TLP:CLEAR — Traffic Light Protocol

This material (intelligence assessment, indicators of compromise, and detection
content) is released TLP:CLEAR. Recipients may share it without restriction,
subject to standard copyright rules and the attribution request below.

PERMITTED
- Use the indicators and detection rules for defensive purposes (detection,
  hunting, blocking, enrichment) in any environment.
- Redistribute, quote, and adapt the material, including in commercial security
  products and services.
- Modify the detection rules to fit local tooling and telemetry.

REQUESTED
- Retain attribution to the author (Yanky Wilson, github.com/yankywilson) when
  redistributing or building upon this material.
- Preserve the confidence levels, estimative-likelihood language, and EXCLUDED
  findings when reproducing the assessment, so calibration is not lost in transit.

ANALYTIC STANDARD
- Confidence levels and estimative likelihoods follow ICD-203. They are the
  author's own analytic judgments, derived from passive OSINT and on-chain
  analysis, and may differ from vendor assessments cited herein.

NO WARRANTY
- This material is provided "as is," without warranty of any kind. Indicators
  reflect point-in-time observations; hosting and resolution data change over
  time. Validate before operational use. The author accepts no liability for
  any use of this material.

Detection rule syntax (Sigma, Suricata, YARA) follows the conventions of the
respective open-source projects and is intended for use within those frameworks.
